## 2. 🔄 Consistency

### 2.1 Branding Fragmentation (Critical)

The codebase has a **significant identity split** between two brands:

| Brand | Where It Appears | Count |
|-------|-----------------|-------|
| **"Solpranos"** | `README.md`, `index.js` (NFT voting messages), `server.js` (CORS origins, session secret, verification message), `nftService.js` (mock NFTs), `battleService.js` (6+ flavor text references), docs, deploy notes | 40+ references |
| **"Guild Pilot"** / **"GuildPilot"** | `ecosystem.config.cjs` (PM2 app name), `embedBranding.js` (default `brandName`), all minigame services, `moduleGuard.js`, `portal.js`, `server.js` (CORS, footers) | 50+ references |

> [!WARNING]
> The bot operates under two names simultaneously. The PM2 process is `guildpilot`, CORS whitelists both `guildpilot.app` and `the-solpranos.com`, and embed footers default to "Powered by Guild Pilot" while battle flavor text references "the Solpranos family."

**Recommendation:** Decide on the canonical brand name and replace all instances. The branding service (`embedBranding.js`) should be the single source of truth — all hardcoded strings should be replaced with `getBranding()` calls.

### 2.2 Module Naming Inconsistencies

| Location | Key Naming | Issue |
|----------|-----------|-------|
| `commandModules.js` | `wallettracker`, `nfttracker`, `tokentracker` | Lowercase, no separator |
| `settings.js` module toggles | `moduleNftTrackerEnabled`, `moduleTokenTrackerEnabled` | camelCase with "module" prefix |
| `moduleGate.js` DISPLAY_NAMES | `'wallettracker': 'Wallet Tracker'` | Lowercase key → title-case display |
| `moduleGuard.js` moduleNames | `'tokentracker': 'Token Activity Tracker'` | **Differs** from moduleGate's `'tokentracker': 'Token Tracker'` |
| `plans.js` MODULE_KEYS | `'wallettracker'`, `'nfttracker'` | Consistent |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> `moduleGuard.js:121` defines `tokentracker` as **"Token Activity Tracker"** but `moduleGate.js:10` defines it as **"Token Tracker"**. The admin sees a different name depending on which gate fires.

### 2.3 Duplicate Logic: `moduleGate.js` vs `moduleGuard.js`

These two files serve overlapping purposes:

| File | Purpose | Pattern |
|------|---------|---------|
| [moduleGate.js](file:///c:/Users/Roland/OneDrive%20-%20Kleermaker/Cartoon%20Maffia%20DAO/roland-discord-bot/middleware/moduleGate.js) | Middleware for interactions — checks if module is enabled | `getCompatibleModuleKeys()` |
| [moduleGuard.js](file:///c:/Users/Roland/OneDrive%20-%20Kleermaker/Cartoon%20Maffia%20DAO/roland-discord-bot/utils/moduleGuard.js) | Utility class — also checks module enable + admin perms | `getModuleCompatibilityKeys()` |

Both define their own display-name maps, both have compatibility-key logic (e.g., wallettracker↔treasury), and both format the same "module disabled" message. This should be consolidated into a single module.

### 2.4 API Response Inconsistency

The codebase has **two parallel response formats**:

| Pattern | Where Used | Format |
|---------|-----------|--------|
| **Legacy inline** `{ success, message }` | `server.js` (95% of routes) | `{ success: true, message: '...' }` |
| **Standardized envelope** `apiResponse.success()` | `routes/v1.js` only | `{ success: true, data: {...}, error: null, meta: {...} }` |

`server.js` line 338 has a comment: *"existing endpoints will be migrated to use apiError/apiSuccess gradually"* — this migration has not happened. The vast majority of the 5,000-line `server.js` still uses the old format.

### 2.5 Config Duplication

| Config | Duplicated In |
|--------|--------------|
| Tier definitions | `config/roles.json` AND `config/settings.json` (identical content) |
| Module toggle defaults | `moduleGuard.js DEFAULT_TOGGLES` AND `config/module-toggles.json` AND `config/settings.js` module flags |

